According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Industrial Pumps Market was valued at USD 68.09 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 96.95 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 5.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to rising investments in water and wastewater treatment infrastructure, increasing industrialization, expanding oil & gas operations, and the growing adoption of energy-efficient smart pumping technologies. As industries worldwide prioritize operational efficiency, environmental compliance, and predictive maintenance, industrial pumps are becoming increasingly critical components across manufacturing, utilities, mining, chemical processing, and power generation sectors.
